{"uid":"4f5ddad22e260cab","name":"test_reseed_deactivation_allows_idempotent_replay_but_rejects_new_posts","fullName":"tests.test_api.TestPostExpense#test_reseed_deactivation_allows_idempotent_replay_but_rejects_new_posts","historyId":"87b5d2e49ffea9be9a0de8b8734e9e76","time":{"start":1777037918476,"stop":1777037918491,"duration":15},"description":"End-to-end of the FK-safe-sync → runtime flow:\n1. Post an expense against an active category so an FK from\n   ``expenses`` to ``categories`` is established.\n2. Simulate the reseed dropping that category from the active\n   vocabulary (``is_active=FALSE``) — the row can't be deleted\n   because the FK still pins it, which is the whole point of\n   the FK-safe algorithm in ``seed_config``.\n3. A truly-new POST (different ``client_expense_id``) against\n   the retired category must return 422.\n4. An idempotent replay (same ``client_expense_id`` + same\n   body) must still return 200 duplicate — an offline PWA\n   retry must not be silently lost to an operator's reseed\n   that happened after the original POST went over the wire.\n","descriptionHtml":"<p>End-to-end of the FK-safe-sync → runtime flow:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Post an expense against an active category so an FK from<br />\n<code>expenses</code> to <code>categories</code> is established.</li>\n<li>Simulate the reseed dropping that category from the active<br />\nvocabulary (<code>is_active=FALSE</code>) — the row can't be deleted<br />\nbecause the FK still pins it, which is the whole point of<br />\nthe FK-safe algorithm in <code>seed_config</code>.</li>\n<li>A truly-new POST (different <code>client_expense_id</code>) against<br />\nthe retired category must return 422.</li>\n<li>An idempotent replay (same <code>client_expense_id</code> + same<br />\nbody) must still return 200 duplicate — an offline PWA<br />\nretry must not be silently lost to an operator's reseed<br />\nthat happened after the original POST went over the wire.</li>\n</ol>\n","status":"passed","fla